latestPosts.caption:
Changes that helped me lose fat ⬇️⬇️

- Eating most of my protein intake during daytime to reduce midnight cravings

- Simplifying my diet into pre decided meals which help me fulfill my protein and caloric goals with ease

- Accurately measuring my food intake (using a kitchen scale, measuring cup etc.)

If you guys have any further questions regarding how I lost weight, feel free to ask in the comments :)

latestPosts.caption:
June dump

Looking back, I can confidently say that this was one of the best months of my life,
After 3 years I’m finally somewhat happy with my physique and my progress.
I’ve also realised the importance of balance and the fact that it’s okay to let loose and have fun (I’d even say it’s a necessity).

If I were to give one piece of advice to any of you, I’d say focus on yourself, be better, grow and eventually, you’ll get everything that you ever asked for AND more. 

Here’s to growth and self improvement! 🥂
